Several Eastern Cape politicians – including premier Phumulo Masualle, former ANCYL leader Ayanda Matiti and former finance deputy minister Mcebisi Jonas – stand a chance to serve on the ANC’s 80member national executive committee (NEC) which is likely to be announced today. They made the cut for final nomination for the NEC in a list presented by the Elections Agency. The NEC vote follows the election of the party’s Top Six on Monday, now led by Cyril Ramaphosa. For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions.      Embattled ANC Nelson Mandela Bay regional chairman Andile Lungisa said he was willing to relinquish his position should the national executive committee (NEC) instruct him to do so today, adding that he was ready to contest for provincial secretary in the July conference scheduled for East London. This comes as… March 27, 2017 Newly elected ANC president Cyril Ramaphosa is not going to have it easy in bringing about reform in the governing party and its ways if the national executive committee (NEC) makeup he serves with is anything to go by. This is according to political analyst Mcebisi Ndletyana who believes that… December 22, 2017 By RANJENI MUNUSAMY and ZINGISA MVUMVU The ANC is finally in position to pin down President Jacob Zuma and now has the ability to hold him accountable and recall him from office. With Cyril Ramphosa’s election as ANC president, Zuma holds no position or authority in the party and therefore… December 21, 2017